ur "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/account\/#\/membership","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Click "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Save","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"p12-Certificate-legacy","text":".p12 Certificate (legacy)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you may utilize Apple’s older authentication scheme ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"type":"text","text":" SSL certificates). Unlike the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"type":"text","text":" solution described above, these certificates automatically expire every year and will require you to regenerate and re-upload them. Braze will send you email reminders as the certificate approaches expiration to help your notifications continue uninterrupted, but because this is a manual process we recommend utilizing the above-described "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p8"},{"type":"text","text":" authentication scheme instead. However, if you still wish to, you may configure and upload "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".p12"},{"type":"text","text":" certificates as described here:"}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"Step-1-Generate-Certificate-Signing-Request","text":"Step 1: Generate Certificate Signing Request"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/ios\/manage\/overview\/index.action","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Identifiers"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in the left sidebar and filter "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"App Ids","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" using the button on the right of the page "},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-identifiers-app-ids.png"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Select your application."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enable push notifications by checking the checkbox then click ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Edit"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-app-id-config.png"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click Create Certificate under the Production SSL Certificate "},{"type":"image","identifier":"apns-certificate-modal.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Production SSL Certificate"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are suitable for App Store and TestFlight builds. Use a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Development SSL Certificate","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for development builds."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Follow the instructions from the SSL certificate assistant.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must update your provisioning profile for the app after you create your SSL certificates. A simple “Refresh” in the organizer will accomplish this."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"text":"Step 2: Export Certificate","type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"Step-2-Export-Certificate"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Download the production push certificate that you just created and open it with the Keychain Access application.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In Keychain Access, click on My Certificates and locate your push certificate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[